description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Successful candidates will be invited to an Assessment Day on Friday 20th November 2020 . Please note this will be either a morning or afternoon session to be confirmed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a motivated, enthusiastic and clinically capable individual to join our nursing team for our 17 bed ward at Stratton Community Hospital. The role requires the post holder to be committed to the ongoing development of the ward and multi disciplinary team working. We aim to deliver the highest standard of patient and rehabilitative care to our predominantly elderly patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal applicant will possess a good level of organisational, communication and clinical skills relevant to the post and be able to act as a positive role model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is working 22.5 hours per week undertaking a range of Early, Late and Night duties on a rotational basis in order to support 24 hour nursing care, 7 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stratton Community Hospital provides an Outpatients Department, X Ray Department and a Minor Injuries Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require a cheerful and enthusiastic individual with a “can-do” attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJacqui HiggittJob titleWard managerEmail addressjhiggitt@nhs.netTelephone number01288 320103Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jacqueline Higgitt Ward Manager Stratton Hospital on 01288 320130&lt;/p&gt;
